         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">16th July 1863. ¶ Dear Dr Mueller, ¶  ¶ I have to congratulate you on the further recognition of the services you have rendered to the cause of science announced in your letter of the 14th inst. ¶  ¶ ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">63.07.16</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Henry Barkly</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Unit 2, p. 14, VPRS 1092 Governor's letter books, VA 466 Governor, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">16th July 1863.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Dr Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have to congratulate you on the further recognition of the services you have rendered to the cause of science announced in your letter of the 14th inst.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As I informed you in regard to the Legion of Honor, it is not in my power to authorize you as a British subject either to accept or wear the Order of Danebrog<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. Dannebrog.</p>
               </note> which H. M. the King of Denmark has been graciously pleased to confer upon you, but I shall have great pleasure now, as then, in applying for the Queen's permission by the next mail.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Believe me</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours faithfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(sd) Henry Barkly</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;c</p>
